    "course_title": "ADVOCATING FOR POPULATIONS: PARTNERING TO IMPROVE COMMUNITY HEALTH",
    "description": "Introduction to advocacy for population health. Covers determinants of health and the systemic causes that specific populations experience with health and health care in the U.S. Explore a range of strategies and tools for creating productive change with, and on behalf of, groups of patients. Strengthen the ability to see connections between the experiences of individual patients and providers and the organizational, political, social, and economic structures that influence the experiences of all health care stakeholders.",
